flag.description: Contains characteristics of an identified security risk.

known_threat_category.name: Trojan
known_threat_category.description: A malicious trojan horse or bot that may represent security risk for the compromised system and/or its network environment

notes_collection.note: %AppData% is a variable that refers to the file system directory that serves as a common repository for application-specific data. A typical path is C:\Documents and Settings\[UserName]\Application Data.
%Temp% is a variable that refers to the temporary folder in the short path form. By default, this is C:\Documents and Settings\[UserName]\Local Settings\Temp\ (Windows NT/2000/XP).
%ProgramFiles% is a variable that refers to the Program Files folder. A typical path is C:\Program Files.
%Windir% is a variable that refers to the Windows installation folder. By default, this is C:\Windows or C:\Winnt.
%System% is a variable that refers to the System folder. By default, this is C:\Windows\System (Windows 95/98/Me), C:\Winnt\System32 (Windows NT/2000), or C:\Windows\System32 (Windows XP).
